tools for OS X 10.9 to install install:

* install homebrew: http://brew.sh/
* $ brew tap homebrew/versions
* $ brew install cmake
* $ brew install gcc48
* $ brew install boost

In downloaded cryptominisat homedir:
* $ mkdir build
* $ cd build
* $ export CXX=`which clang++`
* $ export CPP=/usr/local/bin/g++-4.8
* cmake ../
* make -j4

You now have the 'cryptominisat3' executable in build/

--
Many thanks to Jonathan Heusser who sent me this howto and who
spent time finding compilation bugs for the above to work
